01:57:58,001 --> 01:57:59,309
Papa.

1346
01:58:25,662 --> 01:58:26,868
Rudy?

1347
01:58:42,346 --> 01:58:44,257
<i>(WEAKLY) Saumensch.</i>

1348
01:58:45,649 --> 01:58:46,753
Liesel.

1349
01:58:47,050 --> 01:58:48,256
(SHUSHES)

1350
01:58:51,388 --> 01:58:52,560
I need to tell you...

1351
01:58:52,756 --> 01:58:54,201
Don't speak.

1352
01:58:55,092 --> 01:58:56,969
I need to say it.

1353
01:59:01,498 --> 01:59:02,636
L...

1354
01:59:06,870 --> 01:59:08,008
Rudy?

1355
01:59:09,673 --> 01:59:10,777
Rudy, <i>No.</i>

1356
01:59:11,875 --> 01:59:13,286
Rudy, wake up.

1357
01:59:14,178 --> 01:59:15,521
Rudy, <i>No!</i>

1358
01:59:15,712 --> 01:59:18,352
Wake up, Rudy! Rudy, wake up!

1359
01:59:19,183 --> 01:59:20,685
Rudy, kiss me.

1360
01:59:26,356 --> 01:59:30,862
<i>NARRATOR: Rudy, his sou!
just rolled into my arms.</i>

1361
02:00:48,672 --> 02:00:53,121
<i>In my job, lam always finding
humans at their best...</i>

1362
02:00:53,610 --> 02:00:55,487
<i>and their wars t.</i>

1363
02:00:55,679 --> 02:00:58,956
<i>I see their ugliness, and their beauty...</i>

1364
02:00:59,516 --> 02:01:03,487
<i>and I wonder
how the same thing can be both.</i>

1365
02:01:22,572 --> 02:01:23,812
(GRUNTS)

1366
02:01:56,273 --> 02:01:57,308
Liesel!

1367
02:02:15,492 --> 02:02:17,028
(HORNS HONKING)

1368
02:02:41,284 --> 02:02:42,695
(DOOR OPENING)

1369
02:03:00,270 --> 02:03:01,476
Max!

1370
02:03:14,251 --> 02:03:17,255
<i>NARRATOR: I have seen
a great many things.</i>

1371
02:03:17,454 --> 02:03:20,765
<i>I've attended
all the world's worst disasters...</i>

1372
02:03:20,957 --> 02:03:23,904
<i>and worked for the greatest of villains.</i>

1373
02:03:24,494 --> 02:03:27,475
<i>And I've seen the greatest wonders.</i>

1374
02:03:27,831 --> 02:03:30,641
<i>But it's still like I said it was.</i>

1375
02:03:30,834 --> 02:03:33,508
<i>No one lives forever.</i>

1376
02:03:41,711 --> 02:03:44,692
<i>When I finally came for Liesel...</i>

1377
02:03:44,881 --> 02:03:47,384
<i>I took selfish pleasure in the knowledge</i>

1378
02:03:47,484 --> 02:03:50,954
<i>that she had lived her 90 years so wisely.</i>

1379
02:03:57,861 --> 02:04:01,968
<i>By then, her stories
had touched many souls.</i>

1380
02:04:02,165 --> 02:04:05,271
<i>Some of whom I came to know in passing.</i>

1381
02:04:10,974 --> 02:04:16,117
<i>Max, whose friendship lasted
almost as long as Liesel.</i>

1382
02:04:17,013 --> 02:04:18,617
<i>Almost.</i>

1383
02:04:21,551 --> 02:04:23,553
<i>In her final thoughts...</i>

1384
02:04:23,753 --> 02:04:28,133
<i>she saw the long list of lives
that merged with hers.</i>

1385
02:04:28,892 --> 02:04:30,371
<i>Her three children.</i>

1386
02:04:30,560 --> 02:04:32,471
<i>Her grandchildren.</i>

1387
02:04:32,662 --> 02:04:34,664
<i>Her husband.</i>

1388
02:04:35,265 --> 02:04:37,871
<i>Among them, lit like lanterns...</i>

1389
02:04:38,068 --> 02:04:40,309
<i>were Hans and Rosa...</i>

1390
02:04:40,504 --> 02:04:41,847
<i>her brother...</i>

1391
02:04:42,038 --> 02:04:47,044
<i>and the boy whose hair
remained the color of lemons forever.</i>

1392
02:04:49,746 --> 02:04:51,487
<i>I wanted to tell the book thief</i>

1393
02:04:51,581 --> 02:04:53,254
<i>she was one of the few souls...</i>

1394
02:04:53,450 --> 02:04:57,262
<i>that made me wonder what it was to live.</i>

1395
02:04:58,188 --> 02:05:01,431
<i>But in the end, there were no words.</i>

1396
02:05:01,625 --> 02:05:03,366
<i>Only peace.</i>

1397
02:05:04,427 --> 02:05:07,431
<i>The only truth I truly know...</i>

1398
02:05:07,631 --> 02:05:12,239
<i>is that I am haunted by humans.</i>

